@{b}(c) 2009 Retrami Software@{ub}

@endnode

@node INTRO "Introduction"
Calcumalator is a simple floating point calculator that can be opened on
any public screen of your choosing and will adjust to the appearance and
aspect ratio of that screen.

It is a small tool that is also a commodity and provides an ARexx port so that
it can be made available by any program that has opened on a public screen.
@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"
* Standard installation of AmigaOS 2.04 or better
* That's all, but to get full functionality RexxMast should to be running
  although it is not essential
@endnode

@node FEATURES "Features"
* Works on any version of AmigaOS from 2.04 and up
* Works under AmigaOS 4.x
* GUI adjusts to screen's aspect ratio
* Cut & Paste
* Can open on any public screen and jump between screens
* Runs as a commodity
* Run from Workbench or CLI
* ARexx port
* Supports Localisation
* How many more features can there be on a simple calculator?
@endnode

@node INSTALL "Installation"
The program is fully self-contained so no installation is needed.

The program supports all Commodities tooltypes (see Tool Types section) so it
can be placed in WBStartup and set to start but not show the interface in order
to be called up whenever it's needed.
@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"
@{fg fill}@{b}Starting from CLI@{ub}@{fg text}
The program can be run from the CLI but does not detach automatically.
The standard 'run' command is needed if you want to run the program as a
background process.

The following command line options are valid:

@{b}CX_PRIORITY@{ub}
Sets the priority of this commodity compared to other commodities.
Defaults to 0.

@{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}
Sets the popup key combination. Defaults to <CTRL><LEFT ALT>-C.

@{b}CX_POPUP@{ub}
Determines whether the calculator window is shown on startup. Defaults to "yes".

@{b}XPOS@{ub}
Sets the horizontal position of the window on startup. Defaults to far left.

@{b}YPOS@{ub}
Sets the vertical position of the window on startup. Defaults to just below the
menu bar.

@{b}SCREENNAME@{ub}
The name of the public screen you want the calcumalator to open on at startup.
Defaults to "Workbench"


@{fg fill}@{b}Starting from Workbench@{ub}@{fg text}
When starting from Workbench, all the options mentioned above are honoured if
supplied as ToolTypes.


@{fg fill}@{b}User Interface@{ub}@{fg text}
The window is presented as a standard calculator layout, with clear/reset and
memory store/clear at the top, operators down the right hand side, and the
numbers in the usual position to the left. The number and operand buttons can
also be activated from the keyboard and keypad.

The display at the top supports up to 10 characters on entry, whether or not
there is a fraction entered.

The close button only hides the window. Use @{i}<LEFT AMIGA> Q@{ui}, "@{i}Quit@{ui}" from the
"@{i}Project@{ui}" menu or @{i}<CTRL>-C@{ui} to quit the program.

The menu is laid out as follows:

@{b}Project@{ub}
	@{b}About...@{ub}
		Program information.
	@{b}Hide@{ub}
		Hides the window. Can be re-enabled via the hotkey of via the
		Commodities Exchange.
	@{b}Quit@{ub}
		Terinate the program.

@{b}Edit@{ub}
	@{b}Copy@{ub}
		Inputs a number stored on the clipboard.
	@{b}Paste@{ub}
		Places the display contents on the clipboard.

@{b}Options@{ub}
	@{b}Save Window Position@{ub}
		Stores the current window position in the XPOS and YPOS tooltypes in the
		icon. If the icon cannot be accessed, the position is quietly not saved.
	@{b}Clear Window Position@{ub}
		Comments out the current window position stored in the XPOS and YPOS
		tooltypes in the icon. If the icon cannot be accessed, the position is
		quietly not cleared.
	@{b}Jump To -> Next Screen@{ub}
		Closes and reopens the window on the next available public screen.
	@{b}Jump To -> Screen@{ub}
		Presents a requester allowing you to select which public screen to move
		the window to which is accessed via a cycle gadget. Press the "OK"
		button to move to that screen.
@endnode

@node AREXX "ARexx Port"
The ARexx interface is pretty minimal and primarily exists to control the
location and visibility of the main window. There's no real point providing
access to the functionality since the language already has built in maths
functions (der!)

The ARexx port is called @{b}@{fg fill}CALCUMALATOR@{fg text}@{ub} and the following ARexx commands are
supported:

@{b}ABOUT@{ub}
Returns the about string.

@{b}QUIT@{ub}
Terminates the program.

@{b}MOVEWIN <xpos> <ypos>@{ub}
Moves the window position to a new location
@{i}eg) MOVEWIN 200 100@{ui}

@{b}SCREENNAME <public screen name>@{ub}
Closes the window and reopens it on the specified screen (if possible).
@{i}eg) "SCREENNAME MEMACS_01" will open it on the memacs public screen.@{ui}
@endnode

@node BUGS "Bugs & Quirks"
* PROGDIR assign is used, so unless launched from the same directory as the
  tool, position cannot be saved.

* To be continued ;-)
@endnode
